{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1480].
  {panel}

In other areas of JIRA (eg. project version pages), progress bars are shown as 3 colors: grey (no progress), yellow (work in progress) and green (complete).

Could we please see the same progress bars in Portfolio so that our rollups at Epic / Initiative levels demonstrate said progress?

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1477].
  {panel}

Please implement import/export functionality in Portfolio 2.0. It used to work in the older ("classic") version.

The format doesn't matter all that much. It can be XML, JSON, CSV, anything - as long as it works.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1476].
  {panel}

Particularly useful with multiple owners that update same plan. Committing changes can be problematic since the changes can be done by multiple people and you cannot determine which changes I made.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1472].
  {panel}

we are using Portfolio 1.0 to do Epic ranking and plan to move 2.0.  but I found there is no ranking number(simply 1, 2,... to the last item) anymore in the first column.  We like to have that since when we do the grooming meeting, we call out the number where an item shall move to and it's very convenient. We hope to have this again in v2.0.  Or let me know if this is something that we can enable in the view.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1470].
  {panel}

In Portfolio 1.0, people could not be shared between plans, but some people work on multiple projects. Therefore, the only workable method was to create one plan for all projects, then enter all users, skills, themes, initiatives, etc.

We would like to use the 2.0 features, but there is no means of importing/ upgrading/ converting the old data.

As users, we find "recreate all from scratch" to be too painful of an upgrade method.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1468].
  {panel}

desc

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1462].
  {panel}

In classic plans, I would like to save a reference of the estimate of an initiative at a given point in time. This would allow to compare how much it evolved in time.

This feature is already available for Epics. I would like to have the same at Initiative level.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1456].
  {panel}

Currently, it seems to create always a new team for each board selected. After creating the plan, we are forced to go to Team section, remove it and add the shared one.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1454].
  {panel}

As a user I want to have a scheduling option to ignore JIRA issues that do not have an assignee.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1446].
  {panel}

One of our customer wants to have the ability to define quantity limited resources in Portfolio and assign them to an issue so that when Portfolio calculate the plan it can take account of the available resources, if a required resource for an issue is not available then the issue will be pushed off.
One trivial scenario : 3 employees work on three 1 man-days issues and each issue requires a workstation for employee to work on, customer has only 2 workstations available, so in this case it should take two days to finish the work instead of just one day.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1443].
  {panel}

Standard plans allow three different metrics to evaluate progress.
It would be very important to enable the same metrics in Live plans, too.

As far as I see, currently the only option is the so-called "Time spent". This is not good for us, as we do not recommend teams to track time using the time spent but rather original/remaining estimate.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1440].
  {panel}

I would like to be able to export the Gantt chart created by the Portfolio plugin so that I can re-use the graphic overview for other purposes (eg in Powerpoint). Currently, I can only do so using a screenshot. It would be great to be able to export to a file format like Excel or MS Project so that after export I can than further optimise the gantt chart  for presentation purposes. Having said that, a simple PDF export would be a nice first step.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1439].
  {panel}

Provide users an option to include sprint timeline from capacity view for Epic/Initiative view.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1434].
  {panel}

If the initiative type is set to "New Feature" and you try to import into a portfolio, the New Feature is imported by default as an Epic.  

You can manually change it to Initiative during the import, but then the Epics that are linked to it are not linked as part of the import.

This can be resolved manually, but it is very time and error prone.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1432].
  {panel}

As I try out Portfolio I've created five separate Portfolios. Some are Live, some are variations of the earlier versions. Each time I have to recreate the teams, skills, themes, etc. 

Being able to copy/dupe/clone, then modify from that would be a huge timesaver and probably encourage more experimentation and/or creative use of the tool.

Consistency is hard to maintain when you're building all that stuff from scratch on 18 projects.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1427].
  {panel}

After creating a team it is not possible to change the avatar of a shared team. It would be nice to set a picture like the user or project avatars.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1425].
  {panel}

At present, if multiple releases in a plan have release dates fixed to one date, only a the name of a single release is displayed on the schedule. We would like all releases to be listed, or an icon to expand indicating that there are additional releases on the date.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1424].
  {panel}

The current warning message that shows up when removing items from the backlog table does not explicitly state that all children of an item will be deleted too. This is confusing, raises wrong expectations and might therefore in the worst case lead to data loss.

Hence we should update the error message to explicitly state that all children of this item will be deleted too. We could even mention that it would be a good idea to run a plan export before performing the deletion to prevent data loss in case something was deleted accidentally.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1422].
  {panel}

Capacity views are a critical piece of planning and reporting. The view available in standard plans provided a valuable view, and should be brought forward to Live Plans.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1421].
  {panel}

Currently, an individual user can customize how a plan looks by choosing what to display. (Ex: Issue Link, Issue Status, etc). However, it would be nice to have a view preservation option tied to each plan - this way when anyone brings up the plan he/she can see the same view.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1419].
  {panel}

We have implemented custom columns in our Kanban Boards. 

In Portfolio we can't see any changes in progress for our tasks if the issue changes status to our customised column in Kanban Board. 

I think it should be visible, that some work on this or that issue was done, but the task wasn't completed yet.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1416].
  {panel}

After a few weeks of noodling I'm really pleased with Portfolio and intend to use it to communicate a roadmap to our board of directors, among other helpful activities.

For the BoD, seeing each project's timeline with releases is sufficient detail, especially with Themes adding useful context. However with 20+ projects, epics are too much detail and clutter up the otherwise informative timeline.

Having Epics under the Schedule Settings would be super, alternatively where you can select to display Epics or Stories have the option of displaying neither.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1410].
  {panel}

The "Manage shared teams" page in the Portfolio Team Management does not return all shared teams. 
However, a team that is not included in the list can be found when searching for the team's title.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1408].
  {panel}

few projects can be done in the paid version for 10 users?

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1401].
  {panel}

Allow to statically assign work items to the auto-created "Later" release. 
Currently, static assignments are only possible for explicitly defined releases. 

(Capability to assign items to "Later" exists in standard plans)

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1400].
  {panel}

Clicking an issue in the scope section and having an issue detail panel (like the issue navigator, and JIRA service desk) would be great. Even a configurable panel like JIRA Agile would be helpful.

At the moment if I want to see more information about an item I need to switch context from the Portfolio plan as the issue key links to the full JIRA view of an issue.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1399].
  {panel}

The commit section is not intuitive in regards to clicking the issue key to see what the change is - we expected this to link us to the issue in JIRA so did not pick up that we could view the change until we watched the video. Perhaps have a link next to each ticket on the commit screen to "view change" rather than the user clicking the key?

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1398].
  {panel}

When the roadmap view is broken down to sprints and stages, it would be good if clicking the name of the sprint gave you additional information (like start and end dates, summary info on how much work is open/in progress/done etc), or linked to view the sprint in JIRA Agile (when the sprint exists in JIRA Agile)

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1397].
  {panel}

It would be great to be able to adjust the order of columns in the scope view

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1396].
  {panel}

We would like the ability to add and roll up (where values are numeric) additional columns in the scope section including custom and calculated/scripted custom fields. 

Multiple saved views for the scope section would also be useful if additional columns are allowed (e.g. 2-3 different options with different columns available for each, rather than users needing to add and remove columns to change views)

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1395].
  {panel}

When a sprint is closed in JIRA Agile, the progress against the epic in JIRA Portfolio disappears and the story is no longer visible.

As stories that are in closed sprints are still part of the epic their completion should be taken into account for the epic's progress bar and the stories should remain visible in Portfolio.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1394].
  {panel}

At present there is no prompt to add a plan name when a plan is being created, once it's created it's just called "Untitled plan" unless the user remembers to change it.

This makes it hard for users to find their plans again if other people have also forgotten to name theirs, so we end up with multiple untitled plans. 

This would be resolved by making it mandatory to set a name for the plan - or even having a field during the wizard to prompt users to fill it in

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1393].
  {panel}

During the creation of the Live LABS plans, there is no place to enter a description and there is no place to edit the description after the plan is created.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1392].
  {panel}

At the moment, in case too many backlog items are manually assigned to a release with a fixed end date, the release date gets pushed back and makes the release show up as overbooked and in red. However, the issues that don't fit in are scheduled after the fixed release date.

In some cases customers want to have all manually assigned items to be scheduled before the fixed release date and hence cause the respective sprints / Kanban weeks of that release to be overbooked (i.e., a similar behaviour as we have at the moment when manually assign items to a sprint but on a release level).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1391].
  {panel}

The releases report will be much more useful if sorting options are available where one can choose to show the cards in release date order.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1390].
  {panel}

Currently when committing a live plan, issue assignments made by the scheduling algorithm are not saved to JIRA's assignee field. This suggestion is to add the ability to update the assignee on issues when committing.

Note that manual issue assignments _can_ be committed to JIRA, if the *Commit issue assignee* plan configuration option is enabled. This suggestion is about committing automatic/scheduled assignments to JIRA.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1389].
  {panel}

It would be great to have the ability to auto assign issues to members who already worked on the task.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1385].
  {panel}

If the language specified in the user's profile uses commas for the decimal mark, Portfolio cannot commit story point changes. This is because Portfolio uses the decimal point for story points when it should be using commas instead.

Until this is fixed, the only workaround is to change the user's language to something that uses the decimal point (e.g. English).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1379].
  {panel}

As a Jira Administrator and Scrum Master for my organization,
I want an out-of-the-box dependency mapping tool for visualizing and managing portfolios and complicated projects, so that my colleagues and I can better track dependencies and system integrations, and so that my colleagues will shut up about Rally being a more powerful product.

(linking stories is fine for smaller projects, but it doesn't scale for a SAFe framework)

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1378].
  {panel}

Want to be able to add hierarchy levels that aren't mapped to issue types and that aren't pushed to JIRA/Agile boards.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1377].
  {panel}

Use case: To have a global availability and to switch team members between different teams. So I need to reduce the availability for a certain period for a particular period

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1375].
  {panel}

Currently security has 'Administrators' and 'Read Only' users. Those that have administrators it would be useful to restrict those who have the ability to update the Portfolio plans from having the ability to push data/information back to JIRA (making it one directional).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-1374].
  {panel}

Having the ability to see the priority icon visible on the chart (even though there is limited retail space to view it) would provide a lot of value when viewing along with the current information.
